To the Supervisor of Records,

Pursuant to M.G.L. c.66 =C2=A710A and 950 CMR 32.08, I respectfully submit =
this
appeal regarding the failure of Attleboro Public Schools to respond to a
public records request.

On February 18, 2026, I submitted a public records request to Attleboro
Public Schools seeking records maintained by the district. As of today,
more than ten business days have passed, and I have not received a
response, acknowledgement, fee estimate, or written notice of any extension
as required under the Massachusetts Public Records Law.

The statute requires that a records custodian respond within ten business
days of receiving a request, either by producing the records, denying the
request with a citation to a specific exemption, or providing a written
explanation and estimated timeline for production.

Because Attleboro Public Schools has failed to comply with this statutory
obligation, I respectfully request that the Supervisor of Records:

=E2=80=A2 Issue a determination regarding the district=E2=80=99s failure to=
 respond.
=E2=80=A2 Order Attleboro Public Schools to provide a response and produce
responsive records.
=E2=80=A2 Remind the district of its obligations under M.G.L. c.66 =C2=A710=
 and the
regulations at 950 CMR 32.00.

I would also note that this delay appears to be part of a recurring
pattern. In multiple instances, Attleboro Public Schools has failed to
respond to public records requests within the statutory timeline, requiring
follow-up or appeal. This pattern raises concerns regarding the district=E2=
=80=99s
compliance with the Public Records Law.

A copy of the original request is attached for reference.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Sincerely,

Joey Ford

